# Issue Tracking

Whenever we encounter an error, bug, or unexpected behavior during development, document it in `ISSUES.md` in the project root.

## When to Log

- Deployment or compilation errors
- Runtime errors or unexpected behavior
- Configuration problems
- Any obstacle that required debugging or a workaround

## Format

```markdown
## YYYY-MM-DD — Short issue title

**Problem**: What went wrong (error message, unexpected behavior, etc.)

**Cause**: Why it happened (if known).

**Resolution**: What we did to fix it.
```

## Rules

- New entries go at the top of the file (newest first).
- Keep each section brief -- a few sentences, not paragraphs.
- Include the actual error message or key snippet when relevant.
- If `ISSUES.md` does not exist yet, create it with a top-level `# Issues & Resolutions` heading.
- Log the issue as soon as it's resolved, not retroactively.

## Example

```markdown
# Issues & Resolutions

## 2026-04-08 — Sandbox authentication failed

**Problem**: `sf org login web` returned `INVALID_LOGIN` when trying to connect to the sandbox.

**Cause**: Used `login.salesforce.com` instead of `test.salesforce.com` — sandboxes require the test login URL.

**Resolution**: Re-ran the auth command with `--instance-url https://test.salesforce.com` and login succeeded.
```
